   1426           * @details
   1427           *    The configuration will be set to use a bitrate less than or equal to the desired bitrate
   1428           *    to ensure that the bitrate does not exceed the requested value.
   1429           *
   1430           *    For USART peripherals, fractional clock division is suppressed
   1431           *    in synchronous mode by this function, even though the hardware allows it.
   1432           *    This restriction prevents timing violations causing framing errors and data corruption at high frequencies.
   1433           *    The fractional clock division modifies the clock cycles to average out around the desired bitrate,
   1434           *    adjusting some half periods clock cycle count.
   1435           *    Fractional divider affects the duty cycle of the SCLK, impact is greater at high bitrates where there are few clock cycle count per
   1436           *    half period, and can cause timing issues like MISO setup time violations.
   1437           *    The clock divider will be set to an integer value, so the reference clock
   1438           *    will only be divided by 2N (where N is a positive integer).
   1439           *
   1440           *    For example, if the reference clock is 39 MHz, the maximum baudrate would be 19.5 MHz (RefClock/2).
   1441           *    If the baudrate is set to 19.5 MHz, the clock divider will be set to 0 and the baudrate will be 19.5 MHz.
   1442           *    If the baudrate is [9.75 - 19.5[ MHz, the clock divider will be set to 1, and the actual baudrate will be (RefClock/4) = 9.75 MHz.
   1443           *    If the baudrate is [6.5 - 9.75[ MHz, the clock divider will be set to 2, and the actual baudrate will be (RefClock/6) = 6.5 MHz.
   1444           *    If the baudrate is [4.875 - 6.5[ MHz, the clock divider will be set to 3, and the actual baudrate will be (RefClock/8) = 4.875 MHz.
   1445           *
   1446           *    SPIDRV_GetBitrate will return the actual baudrate according to the USART peripheral configuration.
