   2396          /***************************************************************************//**
   2397           * @brief Wait for transfer completion.
   2398           *
   2399           * When the DMA IRQ is unmasked, the transfer completion is signaled by the
   2400           * regular DMA IRQ -> RxDMAComplete -> BlockingComplete callback chain, so we
   2401           * just spin on the flag.
   2402           *
   2403           * When the DMA IRQ is masked (e.g. caller is inside a critical section), no
   2404           * IRQ will fire to drive that callback chain. We instead poll the DMA Channel
   2405           * Driver via @ref sli_dma_channel_process_completed, which performs the same
   2406           * descriptor processing the IRQ would have. This keeps SPIDRV decoupled from
